  "text": "The pass-through filter implementation follows the established Envoy HTTP filter extension patterns. The core interface StreamDecoderFilter is defined in envoy/http/filter.h (lines 904-955), which specifies the pure virtual methods: decodeHeaders, decodeData, decodeTrailers, and setDecoderFilterCallbacks. The StreamFilterBase (inherited by StreamDecoderFilter) defines the onDestroy() method. Return types FilterHeadersStatus, FilterDataStatus, and FilterTrailersStatus are enums that control filter chain iteration. The filter factory pattern uses the FactoryBase template class from source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h, which inherits from CommonFactoryBase and NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory. Filters are registered using the REGISTER_FACTORY macro with the factory class and Server::Configuration::NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory base class. Examples of complete filter implementations were studied including: buffer filter (source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/), geoip filter (source/extensions/filters/http/geoip/), and health_check filter (source/extensions/filters/http/health_check/). Each filter follows the pattern of: (1) a filter class inheriting from Http::StreamDecoderFilter (or Http::StreamFilter for dual codec filters), (2) implementing all pure virtual methods from the interface, (3) a config factory class inheriting from Common::FactoryBase<ProtoType>, and (4) registration via REGISTER_FACTORY or LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY macros. The implementation provided creates a minimal pass-through filter that returns Continue status for all frame types (headers, data, trailers), allowing requests to pass through the filter chain without modification."
}

